 SP Mojeed Salami, the D.P.O of Seme Police Division in Lagos State has passed away after he slumped in his office on 10th of January. It was gathered that the deceased had complained of headache on the said day & had visited the hospital National Daily reports that sources disclosed the DPO returned to his office a few hours later & resumed work, but that hours later he called his orderly & complained that he was feeling somehow. According to the source, “He asked his orderly to call the Divisional Crime Officer (DCO). I think he wanted to hand over to the DCO. The orderly met him on the floor gasping for breath. He was rushed to the Badagry General Hospital where he was confirmed dead Confirming his death, the Lagos police spokesman, Benjamin Hundeyin, said, “It was shocking to everybody because there was nothing serious about his health. They said he just complained about a minor headache, went to the hospital, came back, commenced work & died shortly afterward